For all this we will need a Python library called Tweepy for accessing the Twitter API. We can install tweepy in three ways:
(i) Using pip command: '$ pip install tweepy'

(ii) Clone the GitHub repository of tweepy: 
$ git clone https://github.com/tweepy/tweepy.git
$ cd tweepy
$ pip install

(iii) Cloning the repository directly:
$ pip install git+https://github.com/tweepy/tweepy.git
